## 4. Steering Configuration & Skills Index

## 4.1 Steering Configuration

- Load the entire `.kiro/steering/` folder as project memory for context.
- Default steering files:
  - `product.md` – product vision, user stories, value.
  - `tech.md` – technical stack, constraints, patterns.
  - `structure.md` – project structure, layering, naming rules.
- Custom steering files are supported and are managed via `/kiro:steering-custom`.

## 4.2 Authority Anchors

- Each relevant steering file MUST contain **Authority Anchors** that point to exact `docs/*.md` or `docs/skills/*.md` sections.

- Example format (in steering file):

  ```
  text
  Authority Anchors:
  - docs/auth/login.md#http-api
  - docs/structure/services.md#auth-service
  - docs/skills/auth/login-flow.md
  ```

- When there is a conflict:

  - `docs/` and `docs/skills/` (authority)

    > active spec docs
    >
    > > steering summary
    > >
    > > > existing code shape.
    > >
    > > ## 4.3 Skills Index (Optional but Recommended)
    > >
    > > - Maintain a skill index in steering (e.g. `tech.md` or `structure.md`):
    > >
    > >   ```
    > >   text
    > >   Skills Index:
    > >   - auth/login-flow  -> docs/skills/auth/login-flow.md
    > >   - auth/token-lifecycle -> docs/skills/auth/token-lifecycle.md
    > >   - billing/reconciliation-core -> docs/skills/billing/reconciliation-core.md
    > >   ```
    > >
    > > - For each spec or task, reference skills by name instead of raw file paths when possible.
